## Content Quality Standards

### Abstract Requirements
- **Length**: 150-300 words for optimal readability
- **Structure**: Context → Problem → Approach → Results → Impact
- **Language**: Clear, accessible to interdisciplinary audience
- **Keywords**: Include relevant technical terms for searchability
- **Novelty**: Highlight unique contributions and innovations

### Biography Standards
- **Focus**: Professional achievements and research expertise
- **Relevance**: Emphasize areas related to lab's research interests
- **Currency**: Use recent achievements and current positions
- **Accessibility**: Avoid excessive jargon, explain specialized terms
- **Contact**: Include collaboration opportunities where appropriate

### Image and Media Guidelines
- **Featured Image**: Professional headshot or event photo
- **Format**: JPEG for photos, PNG for graphics with transparency
- **Resolution**: Minimum 800x600px for featured images
- **File Size**: Optimize for web (<1MB recommended)
- **Alt Text**: Include descriptive alt text for accessibility

## Content Creation Workflow

### Pre-Seminar Preparation

1. **Directory Setup**
   ```bash
   mkdir "/data/seminar/YY-MM-DD-[SpeakerName]"
   cd "/data/seminar/YY-MM-DD-[SpeakerName]"
   ```

2. **Initial Content Creation**
   - Request speaker bio and abstract in advance
   - Obtain high-quality speaker photo
   - Create initial `index.md` with confirmed details
   - Set up placeholder files for slides and materials

3. **Content Review Process**
   - Verify all speaker information accuracy
   - Proofread abstract and biography
   - Confirm seminar logistics (time, location, format)
   - Test any technical requirements (video links, slides)

### Post-Seminar Updates

1. **Material Collection**
   - Upload presentation slides (with speaker permission)
   - Add photos from the event
   - Include any supplementary materials shared
   - Update with recording links if available

2. **Content Enhancement**
   - Add Q&A highlights from the session
   - Include participant feedback if notable
   - Update references with any mentioned resources
   - Add follow-up contact information if provided

3. **Quality Assurance**
   - Verify all links are functional
   - Ensure proper image optimization
   - Validate YAML front-matter syntax
   - Check for consistent formatting

## Archive Organization

### Chronological Categorization
- **Current Year**: Active seminars with full details
- **Previous Years**: Archived seminars with preserved content
- **Special Series**: Workshops, defense presentations, industry talks

### Metadata Management
- Maintain consistent tagging for research areas
- Track seminar series and recurring themes
- Document collaboration outcomes and follow-ups
- Preserve historical context and significance

## Integration with Website Systems

### Automatic Processing
- Seminar listings are dynamically generated from directory structure
- Date-based sorting enables chronological display
- Featured images create visual seminar galleries
- YAML metadata enables filtering and search functionality

### Cross-Reference Capabilities
- Link seminars to related team member research
- Connect to relevant publications and projects
- Reference related laboratory activities
- Integrate with news and announcement systems

## SEO and Discoverability

### Search Optimization
- Include relevant keywords in titles and abstracts
- Use descriptive filenames for all media
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (H1, H2, H3)
- Add meta descriptions through YAML front-matter

### External Visibility
- Format content for academic search engines
- Include speaker institutional affiliations
- Reference related research publications
- Maintain consistent URL structure for citations

## Maintenance and Quality Control

### Regular Review Schedule
- **Monthly**: Verify current seminar information
- **Quarterly**: Review and update speaker contact information
- **Annually**: Archive old seminars and update categorization
- **As needed**: Fix broken links and update references

### Backup and Preservation
- Version control all content changes through Git
- Maintain backup copies of presentation materials
- Preserve speaker permissions and usage rights
- Document any content removal or modification requests

### Accessibility Compliance
- Provide alt text for all images
- Ensure proper heading structure for screen readers
- Include transcripts for video content when available
- Test content with accessibility validation tools

### Analytics and Improvement
- Track seminar page views and engagement
- Monitor download statistics for materials
- Collect feedback on content organization
- Implement improvements based on user behavior data
